aspire /əˈspaɪə/

(aspiring,aspired,aspires) 

1. V-I If you aspire to something such as an important job, you have a strong desire to achieve it. 有志 (于) 

例： ...people who aspire to public office. …志在获得公职的人们。 

例： Rice aspired to go to college. 赖斯渴望上大学。 

2.  →  see also aspiring

